REST API built with **Node.js + Express + TypeScript**.

* CRUD operations for personal notes
* Users entity
* Filtering, sorting and pagination via query parameters
* Request logging middleware
* Centralized error handling
* DTO-based request/response structure

# Project Structure

src
 ├ index.ts
 ├ routes
 ├ controllers
 ├ services
 ├ repositories
 ├ dtos
 └ middleware


# Architecture follows layered pattern:
routes → controllers → services → repositories

# Installation
Clone repository and install dependencies

npm install

# Running the server

Development mode:
npm run dev

Production build:

npm run build
npm start

Server will run on:

http://localhost:3000

# API Endpoints

## Users
GET users
GET /api/users
Create user
POST /api/users
Example body:
{
  "name": "John",
  "email": "john@email.com"
}

## Personal Notes
Get notes
GET /api/personal-notes
Get note by id
GET /api/personal-notes/:id
Create note
POST /api/personal-notes
Example body:
{
  "userId": "demo-user",
  "title": "Math homework",
  "content": "Prepare integrals",
  "teacher": "Ivanov",
  "course": "2",
  "priority": "High"
}
Delete note
DELETE /api/personal-notes/:id

# Query Parameters

Pagination
GET /api/personal-notes?page=1&pageSize=5

Filtering
GET /api/personal-notes?teacher=Ivanov
GET /api/personal-notes?priority=High

Sorting
GET /api/personal-notes?sortBy=createdAt&sortDir=desc

# Error Format

All errors use a consistent format
{
  "error": {
    "code": "VALIDATION_ERROR",
    "message": "teacher, course and priority required"
  }
}

# Example curl tests

Create user

curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/users \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"name":"Test","email":"test@mail.com"}'

Create note

curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/personal-notes \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{"userId":"demo-user","title":"Test","content":"Hello","teacher":"Ivanov","course":"2","priority":"High"}'